WEBVTT

1
00:00:02.367 --> 00:00:05.309
The 20th of July. 1944.

2
00:00:05.333 --> 00:00:06.833
The Wolfsschanze.

3
00:00:07.967 --> 00:00:10.467
Germany's headquarters
on the eastern front.

4
00:00:12.133 --> 00:00:14.609
Nestled away in the
deep forests of Poland.

5
00:00:14.633 --> 00:00:17.076
Adolf Hitler is drawing up plans

6
00:00:17.100 --> 00:00:20.100
that he believes could
secure his victory in Europe.

7
00:00:22.033 --> 00:00:23.443
The führer strategies

8
00:00:23.467 --> 00:00:26.176
are interrupted by a knock at the door.

9
00:00:26.200 --> 00:00:28.476
Colonel Claus von Stauffenberg.

10
00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:31.109
Hitler's trusted chief of staff walks in

11
00:00:31.133 --> 00:00:32.500
holding a briefcase.

12
00:00:34.567 --> 00:00:37.767
But Stauffenberg is not
here to talk battle plans.

13
00:00:39.067 --> 00:00:41.567
he's here to kill Hitler.

14
00:01:07.500 --> 00:01:10.843
There were lots of plots to kill Hitler.

15
00:01:10.867 --> 00:01:12.643
and he survived so many

16
00:01:12.667 --> 00:01:15.076
that it made Hitler feel
that he really did have

17
00:01:15.100 --> 00:01:17.509
this kind of divine providence behind him

18
00:01:17.533 --> 00:01:19.343
that made him survive.

19
00:01:28.400 --> 00:01:30.043
The most celebrated plot against him

20
00:01:30.067 --> 00:01:34.076
was the July bomb plot of July. 1944.

21
00:01:34.100 --> 00:01:37.676
in which you've got this kind
of cadre of senior officers

22
00:01:37.700 --> 00:01:39.076
all over the Third Reich

23
00:01:39.100 --> 00:01:43.033
who have been meeting in
secret for many years actually.

24
00:01:44.733 --> 00:01:49.109
On the 20th of July. 1944.
Claus von Stauffenberg

25
00:01:49.133 --> 00:01:52.943
made a serious attempt
on the Führer's life

26
00:01:52.967 --> 00:01:56.109
by bringing a bomb into the
briefing room where Hitler was.

27
00:01:56.133 --> 00:01:57.409
placing it under his desk

28
00:01:57.433 --> 00:02:00.733
and hoping that it would kill Hitler.

29
00:02:16.400 --> 00:02:17.943
Adolf Hitler.

30
00:02:17.967 --> 00:02:21.300
the most notorious dictator
of the 20th century.

31
00:02:29.800 --> 00:02:32.209
Outraged by the Treaty of Versailles

32
00:02:32.233 --> 00:02:35.409
and Germany's humiliation
in the first World War.

33
00:02:35.433 --> 00:02:36.743
Hitler fiercely campaigned

34
00:02:36.767 --> 00:02:39.467
to rescue the Fatherland from ruin.

35
00:02:42.400 --> 00:02:44.576
The mood in Germany at
the end of World War I

36
00:02:44.600 --> 00:02:49.667
was that of a humiliated and
defeated people and nation.

37
00:02:50.833 --> 00:02:53.443
This fight had been
going on for four years.

38
00:02:53.467 --> 00:02:57.476
Millions of people had died
and no one had got anything.

39
00:02:57.500 --> 00:02:59.267
or no one had got anywhere.

40
00:03:01.433 --> 00:03:04.443
It was a mood of revolution.

41
00:03:04.467 --> 00:03:08.909
a mood of deep dissatisfaction.
a mood of instability.

42
00:03:08.933 --> 00:03:12.943
and it felt like the country
was on the brink of collapse.

43
00:03:12.967 --> 00:03:15.543
His mesmerizing public speeches

44
00:03:15.567 --> 00:03:17.709
called for a new order in Germany.

45
00:03:17.733 --> 00:03:20.643
one which would cast off the
weakened incompetent structure

46
00:03:20.667 --> 00:03:22.643
of the Democratic regime.

47
00:03:22.667 --> 00:03:26.200
and instead install a
supreme national leader.

48
00:03:30.700 --> 00:03:32.943
Citizens from all corners of the country

49
00:03:32.967 --> 00:03:36.243
fell for the relentless
promotion of his ideology.

50
00:03:36.267 --> 00:03:40.809
and Hitler successfully recast
himself as Germany's savior.

51
00:03:40.833 --> 00:03:45.900
What Hitler is absolutely
amazing at is speech making.

52
00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:48.376
And to begin to understand Hitler.

53
00:03:48.400 --> 00:03:50.643
you've really gotta understand

54
00:03:50.667 --> 00:03:54.843
that he was the most
amazing demagogue.

55
00:03:54.867 --> 00:03:58.009
Hitler's speeches are really vitriolic.

56
00:03:58.033 --> 00:03:59.376
but they're very effective.

57
00:03:59.400 --> 00:04:01.643
and they attract regular audiences.

58
00:04:01.667 --> 00:04:05.009
and he's really good at
using populist themes.

59
00:04:05.033 --> 00:04:09.043
And labels scapegoats for losing the war.

60
00:04:09.067 --> 00:04:11.109
You name it. Jews. communists.

61
00:04:11.133 --> 00:04:13.009
you know. whoever Hitler hates.

62
00:04:13.033 --> 00:04:15.343
that given moment. he'll lay into them.

63
00:04:15.367 --> 00:04:17.276
Listeners are listening and watching this.

64
00:04:17.300 --> 00:04:18.776
and they're thinking. yes.

65
00:04:18.800 --> 00:04:20.909
these are the reasons for
our economic hardships.

66
00:04:20.933 --> 00:04:24.809
And Hitler's also got this
huge personal magnetism.

67
00:04:24.833 --> 00:04:27.543
and he's got this
instinctive understanding

68
00:04:27.567 --> 00:04:29.309
of the psychology of crowds.

69
00:04:29.333 --> 00:04:30.843
And of course.

70
00:04:30.867 --> 00:04:32.343
you know. like any really
brilliant public speaker.

71
00:04:32.367 --> 00:04:34.409
he's going to use that to his advantage.

72
00:04:34.433 --> 00:04:36.567
It's like a conductor with an orchestra.

73
00:04:47.733 --> 00:04:49.509
Like many dictators before him.

74
00:04:49.533 --> 00:04:52.143
he became insistent on
protecting his godlike image

75
00:04:52.167 --> 00:04:54.843
and divine right to power.

76
00:04:54.867 --> 00:04:56.309
The Führer kept himself away

77
00:04:56.333 --> 00:05:00.043
from the more violent and
brutal aspects of the regime.

78
00:05:00.067 --> 00:05:02.576
He promoted anti-Jewish propaganda.

79
00:05:02.600 --> 00:05:04.976
but refused to bloody his own hands.

80
00:05:05.000 --> 00:05:07.076
relying instead on his loyal circle

81
00:05:07.100 --> 00:05:09.000
to rid Germany of its enemies me.

82
00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:17.643
So the issue of how Hitler managed

83
00:05:17.667 --> 00:05:19.676
to keep his popular image clean

84
00:05:19.700 --> 00:05:22.609
while the final solution was underway

85
00:05:22.633 --> 00:05:25.709
is obviously a very interesting

86
00:05:25.733 --> 00:05:27.576
and a very difficult question.

87
00:05:27.600 --> 00:05:30.476
But I suppose the essence
of it is two things.

88
00:05:30.500 --> 00:05:32.009
First of all. that those mass shootings

89
00:05:32.033 --> 00:05:37.067
that were taking place in the
USSR were not on German soil.

90
00:05:38.400 --> 00:05:40.676
And of course. the second part.
the most important part too.

91
00:05:40.700 --> 00:05:44.109
that the death camps. all of
those were on Polish soil.

92
00:05:44.133 --> 00:05:46.576
So they were out of the
immediate frame of sight

93
00:05:46.600 --> 00:05:49.243
or reference of the Germans.

94
00:05:49.267 --> 00:05:52.209
So again. in some way. they
were happening elsewhere

95
00:05:52.233 --> 00:05:54.967
and not really in their
immediate field of vision.

96
00:05:59.700 --> 00:06:02.509
Hitler is always mindful of public opinion.

97
00:06:02.533 --> 00:06:06.176
I think that it's always important to
remember that Hitler.

98
00:06:06.200 --> 00:06:08.143
you know. does always worry about

99
00:06:08.167 --> 00:06:09.776
what the German people
think about him.

100
00:06:09.800 --> 00:06:14.209
He doesn't just sort of seize
power in 33 and then not care.

101
00:06:14.233 --> 00:06:16.876
You know. he wants to be
liked. he wants to be popular.

102
00:06:16.900 --> 00:06:18.709
He's a political leader after all.

103
00:06:18.733 --> 00:06:20.843
And all political leaders.

104
00:06:20.867 --> 00:06:24.300
democratic. or fascist or
otherwise. want to be liked.

105
00:06:30.833 --> 00:06:32.409
However. Hitler and the Nazis

106
00:06:32.433 --> 00:06:34.809
were not entirely immune
to the consequences

107
00:06:34.833 --> 00:06:36.567
of their dark agenda.

108
00:06:37.700 --> 00:06:39.643
Feelings of disillusionment and disgust

109
00:06:39.667 --> 00:06:42.009
built up amongst certain individuals.

110
00:06:42.033 --> 00:06:44.076
And by 1944.

111
00:06:44.100 --> 00:06:46.800
Hitler faced the biggest
threat to his life yet.

112
00:06:51.233 --> 00:06:52.476
Out of Hitler's Nazi regime.

113
00:06:52.500 --> 00:06:55.009
spilled not only a drive to preserve

114
00:06:55.033 --> 00:06:58.043
the country's economy and global status.

115
00:06:58.067 --> 00:07:02.233
Nazism also meant the annihilation of
Germany's enemies.

116
00:07:04.100 --> 00:07:08.209
And in 1935. the creation
of the Nuremberg Laws

117
00:07:08.233 --> 00:07:12.176
set its sites firmly on the
most hated group in Germany.

118
00:07:12.200 --> 00:07:13.267
the Jews.

119
00:07:14.367 --> 00:07:15.576
So we know that from as early as.

120
00:07:15.600 --> 00:07:17.043
Hitler's writings in "Mein Kampf."

121
00:07:17.067 --> 00:07:21.076
that he was personally antisemitic.

122
00:07:21.100 --> 00:07:22.743
So we see his personal antisemitism

123
00:07:22.767 --> 00:07:25.267
translated into state policy.

124
00:07:26.633 --> 00:07:29.543
There were many different
measures. legal measures

125
00:07:29.567 --> 00:07:33.276
taken against the Jews. and
also illegal measures as well.

126
00:07:33.300 --> 00:07:34.709
So very early on.

127
00:07:34.733 --> 00:07:37.543
there was a boycott of
Jewish shops and businesses.

128
00:07:37.567 --> 00:07:41.509
Very early on too. there
was a civil service law.

129
00:07:41.533 --> 00:07:44.076
which essentially threw
out Jewish civil servants

130
00:07:44.100 --> 00:07:45.733
from their positions.

131
00:07:47.100 --> 00:07:48.343
The Nuremberg Laws

132
00:07:48.367 --> 00:07:51.343
really put into place
some legal parameters

133
00:07:51.367 --> 00:07:54.643
for how the situation would
be with Germany's Jews.

134
00:07:54.667 --> 00:07:57.343
But what they did really was to turn.

135
00:07:57.367 --> 00:07:59.409
Germany's Jews into
second class citizens.

136
00:07:59.433 --> 00:08:03.209
really to take away their
equal citizenship rights.

137
00:08:03.233 --> 00:08:05.709
And also to forbid marriage
or sexual relations

138
00:08:05.733 --> 00:08:08.200
between Jews and Aryans.

139
00:08:09.567 --> 00:08:12.109
Many citizens bought into the ideology

140
00:08:12.133 --> 00:08:15.867
that the very presence of Jews
threatened the German people.

141
00:08:17.500 --> 00:08:19.276
Ordinary people everywhere

142
00:08:19.300 --> 00:08:22.176
began practicing antisemitic views

143
00:08:22.200 --> 00:08:25.743
and encouraging the idea that
Jews were an inferior race.

144
00:08:25.767 --> 00:08:28.833
separate to the superior Aryan Germans.

145
00:08:58.967 --> 00:09:01.009
Before long. such poisonous rhetoric

146
00:09:01.033 --> 00:09:03.009
turned into violent action.

147
00:09:03.033 --> 00:09:06.009
And on the 9th of November. 1938.

148
00:09:06.033 --> 00:09:09.076
the Nazi regime coordinated
a wave of attacks

149
00:09:09.100 --> 00:09:10.867
across the country.

150
00:09:13.433 --> 00:09:15.876
You suddenly get this
thing called Kristallnacht.

151
00:09:15.900 --> 00:09:18.776
the Night of Broken Glass in 1938.

152
00:09:18.800 --> 00:09:23.676
where the Nazis just literally set fire

153
00:09:23.700 --> 00:09:25.776
to synagogues everywhere.

154
00:09:25.800 --> 00:09:29.009
The world really noticed Kristallnacht.

155
00:09:29.033 --> 00:09:31.143
you know. this absolutely horrific

156
00:09:31.167 --> 00:09:34.309
destruction. slaughter. violence

157
00:09:34.333 --> 00:09:37.943
carried out by the state
against its own people.

158
00:09:37.967 --> 00:09:41.009
It showed the world what Hitler was.

159
00:09:41.033 --> 00:09:43.800
He was effectively a
gangster and a murderer.

160
00:09:47.467 --> 00:09:49.009
The violence was supposed to look

161
00:09:49.033 --> 00:09:52.767
like an unplanned outburst of
popular anger against Jews.

162
00:09:53.767 --> 00:09:55.109
But in reality.

163
00:09:55.133 --> 00:09:59.276
Kristallnacht state-sponsored
vandalism and arson.

164
00:09:59.300 --> 00:10:01.709
Nazi leaders actively coordinated it

165
00:10:01.733 --> 00:10:04.509
with Adolf Hitler's support.

166
00:10:04.533 --> 00:10:06.476
There's no doubt about the centrality

167
00:10:06.500 --> 00:10:08.343
of antisemitism to Hitler's worldview.

168
00:10:08.367 --> 00:10:10.943
There's absolutely no doubt about that.

169
00:10:10.967 --> 00:10:12.309
But what he seemed to be trying to do

170
00:10:12.333 --> 00:10:13.709
was sort of stay in the shadow

171
00:10:13.733 --> 00:10:15.609
so that when we get a pogrom like this.

172
00:10:15.633 --> 00:10:18.209
that the public. the German
public and the population

173
00:10:18.233 --> 00:10:19.709
were quite affronted by it.

174
00:10:19.733 --> 00:10:22.409
Maybe not because they
particularly supported the Jews.

175
00:10:22.433 --> 00:10:25.776
but because it was a kind of
a sort of flagrant violation

176
00:10:25.800 --> 00:10:28.343
of law and order and sort of

177
00:10:28.367 --> 00:10:31.543
a kind of very violent.
violent affair across the land.

178
00:10:31.567 --> 00:10:34.143
So. you know. it wasn't
popular in that respect.

179
00:10:34.167 --> 00:10:35.543
So there's that idea then

180
00:10:35.567 --> 00:10:37.576
that Hitler was sort of
staying in the shadows

181
00:10:37.600 --> 00:10:40.209
and not being associated with that.

182
00:10:40.233 --> 00:10:42.009
I think he managed to
maintain his popularity

183
00:10:42.033 --> 00:10:43.543
during this time.

184
00:10:43.567 --> 00:10:45.943
first of all. because he
was staying in the shadows

185
00:10:45.967 --> 00:10:48.243
of more unpopular policies.

186
00:10:48.267 --> 00:10:49.543
And there was certainly that sentiment

187
00:10:49.567 --> 00:10:51.776
among the German population

188
00:10:51.800 --> 00:10:54.443
because of this myth that
surrounded the führer.

189
00:10:54.467 --> 00:10:57.176
that well. if there were
unpleasant things going on

190
00:10:57.200 --> 00:10:58.876
or policies that they didn't like.

191
00:10:58.900 --> 00:11:01.409
then somehow that Hitler
couldn't know about it.

192
00:11:01.433 --> 00:11:03.476
that he wasn't associated with it.

193
00:11:03.500 --> 00:11:05.733
that it had to be one of the other leaders.

194
00:11:13.333 --> 00:11:15.776
Universal
approval of the violent pogroms

195
00:11:15.800 --> 00:11:18.743
was not a reality for Hitler.

196
00:11:18.767 --> 00:11:21.909
In fact. opposition lurked
in unexpected places

197
00:11:21.933 --> 00:11:24.976
and arose from unexpected individuals.

198
00:11:25.000 --> 00:11:27.143
Major general Henning von Tresckow

199
00:11:27.167 --> 00:11:29.709
absolutely despised the Nuremberg Laws

200
00:11:29.733 --> 00:11:32.500
and the violent Kristallnacht attacks.

201
00:11:34.367 --> 00:11:36.376
From as early as the 1930s.

202
00:11:36.400 --> 00:11:39.176
the Nazi officer had been
plotting Hitler's overthrow

203
00:11:39.200 --> 00:11:41.376
and gathering a trusted circle of people

204
00:11:41.400 --> 00:11:42.933
to assassinate the Führer.

205
00:11:44.367 --> 00:11:47.509
Tresckow's disgust towards
extreme antisemitism.

206
00:11:47.533 --> 00:11:50.476
consequently spurred him on
to become a key architect

207
00:11:50.500 --> 00:11:52.367
of Operation Valkyrie.

208
00:11:56.467 --> 00:11:59.176
Meanwhile. at the graveyard
attached to the institution.

209
00:11:59.200 --> 00:12:01.309
bodies are exhumed for autopsy.

210
00:12:01.333 --> 00:12:03.576
20.000 are buried here.

211
00:12:03.600 --> 00:12:05.776
15.000 who died in a lethal gas chamber

212
00:12:05.800 --> 00:12:08.843
were cremated and their ashes in turd.

213
00:12:08.867 --> 00:12:11.176
Death books found hidden
in the wine cellar

214
00:12:11.200 --> 00:12:14.143
of the Hadamar institution
revealed part of the story

215
00:12:14.167 --> 00:12:15.609
of the mass killings.

216
00:12:15.633 --> 00:12:18.609
The bulky volumes contained
thousands of death certificates.

217
00:12:18.633 --> 00:12:21.376
Profession unknown.
nationality unknown

218
00:12:21.400 --> 00:12:23.433
was written after each name.

219
00:12:24.567 --> 00:12:26.376
Feelings of disenchantment. however.

220
00:12:26.400 --> 00:12:29.809
did not halt with Hitler's
anti-Jewish policies.

221
00:12:29.833 --> 00:12:34.076
In 1939. one of the darkest
programs of the Nazi regime

222
00:12:34.100 --> 00:12:35.667
came into existence.

223
00:12:36.533 --> 00:12:38.867
Aktion T4.

224
00:12:41.533 --> 00:12:45.109
Where Hitler's popularity
starts to take a real dent

225
00:12:45.133 --> 00:12:47.476
is his association.

226
00:12:47.500 --> 00:12:51.009
or the Nazi association with
what is called the T4 program.

227
00:12:51.033 --> 00:12:52.543
Now. the T4 program

228
00:12:52.567 --> 00:12:54.943
is named after the address in
which it was headquartered.

229
00:12:54.967 --> 00:12:57.543
Tiergartenstraße 4 in Berlin.

230
00:12:57.567 --> 00:13:00.776
And it really was the most repellent form

231
00:13:00.800 --> 00:13:03.543
of kind of Nazi quote unquote "medicine"

232
00:13:03.567 --> 00:13:05.033
that you could imagine.

233
00:13:06.167 --> 00:13:07.543
Because it was this idea

234
00:13:07.567 --> 00:13:10.576
that you have to treat a people as a body.

235
00:13:10.600 --> 00:13:13.776
But what if you've got part
of your body as a population

236
00:13:13.800 --> 00:13:15.909
that is considered to be weak.

237
00:13:15.933 --> 00:13:18.109
i.e. sort of cancerous or deformed.

238
00:13:18.133 --> 00:13:21.076
or has hereditary illnesses?

239
00:13:21.100 --> 00:13:22.543
Well. why don't you just
chop them off as well?

240
00:13:22.567 --> 00:13:25.043
Because if you can get rid of them.

241
00:13:25.067 --> 00:13:27.343
i.e. people with congenital problems.

242
00:13:27.367 --> 00:13:31.309
you are gonna stop those
bad genes being passed on.

243
00:13:31.333 --> 00:13:34.709
And that's essentially
what the T4 program is.

244
00:13:34.733 --> 00:13:39.509
It is basically chopping people out of life.

245
00:13:39.533 --> 00:13:40.976
You're killing them.

246
00:13:41.000 --> 00:13:42.776
You're killing children with epilepsy.

247
00:13:42.800 --> 00:13:47.376
You're killing people who've
got mild spinal deformities.

248
00:13:47.400 --> 00:13:50.509
You're killing people
who've even got stutters

249
00:13:50.533 --> 00:13:53.443
because you are saying
they're genetically weak

250
00:13:53.467 --> 00:13:54.976
and we don't want them.

251
00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:57.109
if we're gonna make this
strong. blonde Aryan race

252
00:13:57.133 --> 00:13:59.809
full of perfect super humans.

253
00:13:59.833 --> 00:14:02.833
It's kind of pseudo
medicine. it's pseudoscience.

254
00:14:05.767 --> 00:14:08.243
The unlawful system of mass murder.

255
00:14:08.267 --> 00:14:10.476
outraged many German citizens.

256
00:14:10.500 --> 00:14:12.843
particularly Protestants and Catholics.

257
00:14:12.867 --> 00:14:16.876
who led protests against
the exterminations.

258
00:14:16.900 --> 00:14:19.709
Relatives of patients
everywhere frantically panicked

259
00:14:19.733 --> 00:14:21.743
with many. withdrawing their relatives

260
00:14:21.767 --> 00:14:24.709
from asylums to care for them at home.

261
00:14:24.733 --> 00:14:26.843
In some places. doctors
and psychiatrists

262
00:14:26.867 --> 00:14:28.776
also cooperated with families

263
00:14:28.800 --> 00:14:30.976
to have patients
discharged or transferred

264
00:14:31.000 --> 00:14:34.233
to private clinics beyond the reach of T4.

265
00:14:39.733 --> 00:14:42.143
Führer Chancellery
Director Phillip Bouhler

266
00:14:42.167 --> 00:14:45.700
and physician Karl Brandt
led the killing operation.

267
00:14:47.067 --> 00:14:49.876
Under their leadership.
T4 operatives established

268
00:14:49.900 --> 00:14:52.876
six gassing installations for adults

269
00:14:52.900 --> 00:14:54.933
as part of the euthanasia action.

270
00:14:57.333 --> 00:15:00.376
For every person killed. a
death certificate was prepared.

271
00:15:00.400 --> 00:15:03.109
giving a false. but
plausible cause of death

272
00:15:03.133 --> 00:15:05.133
to hide the evil reality.

273
00:15:07.933 --> 00:15:11.209
Hitler publicly canceled
the program in 1941

274
00:15:11.233 --> 00:15:13.700
after outcry from the German people.

275
00:15:14.767 --> 00:15:16.743
However. the killings in fact. continued

276
00:15:16.767 --> 00:15:19.343
until the end of the war.

277
00:15:19.367 --> 00:15:23.043
By 1945. the Nazis
had callously murdered

278
00:15:23.067 --> 00:15:26.367
as many as 300.000 innocent people.

279
00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:34.409
The T4 euthanasia program

280
00:15:34.433 --> 00:15:36.876
represented in many ways a rehearsal

281
00:15:36.900 --> 00:15:40.700
for Nazi Germany's subsequent
genocidal policies.

282
00:15:41.567 --> 00:15:43.509
Planners of the final solution

283
00:15:43.533 --> 00:15:45.876
later borrowed the gas chamber method

284
00:15:45.900 --> 00:15:48.309
to eradicate the Jewish
and Roma populations

285
00:15:48.333 --> 00:15:52.000
on a scale never before seen in history.

286
00:16:50.300 --> 00:16:53.543
Two years into the largest
conflict in history.

287
00:16:53.567 --> 00:16:56.809
Adolf Hitler devised his riskiest move yet.

288
00:16:56.833 --> 00:16:59.000
Operation Barbarossa

289
00:17:00.300 --> 00:17:04.476
Hitler despised Bolshevism
and Stalin's regime.

290
00:17:04.500 --> 00:17:07.209
Intent on wiping out the Soviet Union.

291
00:17:07.233 --> 00:17:10.609
he ordered Nazi troops to invade
Russian occupied territory

292
00:17:10.633 --> 00:17:12.767
on the 22nd of June. 1941.

293
00:17:35.600 --> 00:17:37.443
Hitler had assured the high command

294
00:17:37.467 --> 00:17:40.609
that we have only to
kick in the front door.

295
00:17:40.633 --> 00:17:43.700
and the whole rotten edifice
will come tumbling down.

296
00:17:44.533 --> 00:17:46.900
But Russia was not France.

297
00:17:48.500 --> 00:17:51.643
Despite the serious losses
inflicted on the Red Army

298
00:17:51.667 --> 00:17:53.876
and extensive territorial gains.

299
00:17:53.900 --> 00:17:56.543
the mission to completely
destroy Soviet fighting power

300
00:17:56.567 --> 00:17:58.743
was not achieved.

301
00:17:58.767 --> 00:18:02.209
The Soviets were not
going to go down easily.

302
00:18:02.233 --> 00:18:04.209
Had Hitler stopped

303
00:18:04.233 --> 00:18:06.076
after he'd successfully
conquered France

304
00:18:06.100 --> 00:18:10.476
and the low countries. and
not decided in June. 1941

305
00:18:10.500 --> 00:18:12.043
that he was going to invade

306
00:18:12.067 --> 00:18:14.643
this really quite big
country called Russia.

307
00:18:14.667 --> 00:18:16.167
he may have stayed in power.

308
00:18:21.967 --> 00:18:24.076
But of course. what Stalin's got

309
00:18:24.100 --> 00:18:25.743
is a lot of room to fight him.

310
00:18:25.767 --> 00:18:28.943
because he can retreat and
retreat and retreat and retreat.

311
00:18:28.967 --> 00:18:33.243
and you've still got thousands
of miles of Russia behind you

312
00:18:33.267 --> 00:18:34.633
that you can fall back on.

313
00:18:36.133 --> 00:18:39.743
But also what Stalin does is
he's very good at regrouping

314
00:18:39.767 --> 00:18:41.743
and getting his forces back together.

315
00:18:41.767 --> 00:18:45.876
Germans use a lot of
over designed tanks.

316
00:18:45.900 --> 00:18:48.543
over designed uniforms.
over designed weapons.

317
00:18:48.567 --> 00:18:50.076
What the Russians are good at doing is

318
00:18:50.100 --> 00:18:52.943
just getting things together
in a kind of makeshift way.

319
00:18:52.967 --> 00:18:55.243
But that works.

320
00:18:55.267 --> 00:18:56.376
You know. everything Russians have.

321
00:18:56.400 --> 00:18:58.743
uniforms. tanks. weaponry.

322
00:18:58.767 --> 00:19:00.176
really simple. really easy to use.

323
00:19:00.200 --> 00:19:03.143
really easy to mass
produce very. very quickly.

324
00:19:03.167 --> 00:19:05.909
German kit takes ages to produce.

325
00:19:05.933 --> 00:19:09.000
So this is another real problem
that's faced by the Germans.

326
00:19:10.933 --> 00:19:13.776
1942 would be an even worse year

327
00:19:13.800 --> 00:19:15.600
for Hitler's fight in the East.

328
00:19:18.533 --> 00:19:19.709
The Führer hoped to take

329
00:19:19.733 --> 00:19:22.943
the strategic city of Stalingrad easily.

330
00:19:22.967 --> 00:19:26.476
but the well-armed Red Army
and the fierce Russian winter

331
00:19:26.500 --> 00:19:29.667
made German soldiers'
lives absolute hell.

332
00:19:41.000 --> 00:19:42.443
By mid-November.

333
00:19:42.467 --> 00:19:45.243
the Germans found themselves
outnumbered. outgunned.

334
00:19:45.267 --> 00:19:48.376
extremely low on food
and medical supplies.

335
00:19:48.400 --> 00:19:50.600
and surrounded by Russians.

336
00:19:51.700 --> 00:19:53.976
But Hitler refused to withdraw troops.

337
00:19:54.000 --> 00:19:57.609
He placed prestige over
lives and commanded

338
00:19:57.633 --> 00:19:59.943
they hold their positions to the last man

339
00:19:59.967 --> 00:20:01.733
and the last round.

340
00:20:02.767 --> 00:20:05.043
He also promised additional provisions.

341
00:20:05.067 --> 00:20:07.676
provisions that never arrived.

342
00:20:07.700 --> 00:20:11.409
So when the tide of
the war turned in 1943

343
00:20:11.433 --> 00:20:13.076
with a battle of Stalingrad

344
00:20:13.100 --> 00:20:15.209
and then the fortunes
went the other way.

345
00:20:15.233 --> 00:20:17.343
then that sort of question
of the infallibility

346
00:20:17.367 --> 00:20:21.033
of the Führer came to
be called into question.

347
00:20:22.100 --> 00:20:26.309
So whilst by this point after Stalingrad.

348
00:20:26.333 --> 00:20:29.043
the cult of the leader
was diminished somewhat.

349
00:20:29.067 --> 00:20:33.343
he'd created this myth
of the Soviet hordes

350
00:20:33.367 --> 00:20:36.676
and this great Soviet
enemy to such an extent

351
00:20:36.700 --> 00:20:40.043
that out of fear and out of desperation.

352
00:20:40.067 --> 00:20:43.576
both the army and the home front

353
00:20:43.600 --> 00:20:48.400
really worked until the bitter
end before capitulation.

354
00:20:50.100 --> 00:20:51.576
Left with little choice.

355
00:20:51.600 --> 00:20:55.309
German general Friedrich Paulus
went against Hitler's orders

356
00:20:55.333 --> 00:20:57.843
and surrendered his
weakened troops to Russia

357
00:20:57.867 --> 00:21:00.343
on February the 2nd 1943.

358
00:21:00.367 --> 00:21:03.500
an act which Hitler later called "treason."

359
00:21:04.900 --> 00:21:07.543
The heavy defeat. punctured
the Führer's power in Europe.

360
00:21:07.567 --> 00:21:09.743
and a lurking feeling of disenchantment

361
00:21:09.767 --> 00:21:12.200
spread throughout the German army.

362
00:21:14.167 --> 00:21:16.776
Stalingrad soon became a major catalyst

363
00:21:16.800 --> 00:21:19.376
for conspirators across the Third Reich

364
00:21:19.400 --> 00:21:22.267
to join the plot to kill Hitler.

365
00:21:28.667 --> 00:21:31.767
Claus von Stauffenberg
was no exception.

366
00:21:33.467 --> 00:21:36.276
He had witnessed firsthand
the absolute catastrophe

367
00:21:36.300 --> 00:21:37.809
on the eastern front

368
00:21:37.833 --> 00:21:41.267
and became convinced that
Hitler had to be removed.

369
00:21:48.333 --> 00:21:51.743
Stauffenberg was born into
an aristocratic family.

370
00:21:51.767 --> 00:21:54.843
Despite joining the
Wehrmacht. he. like many elites.

371
00:21:54.867 --> 00:21:57.633
tended to view the Nazis with this taste.

372
00:22:02.267 --> 00:22:04.743
However. it would not
just be a class issue

373
00:22:04.767 --> 00:22:06.009
that persuaded Stauffenberg

374
00:22:06.033 --> 00:22:08.600
to turn away from his divine leader.

375
00:22:10.300 --> 00:22:12.276
His time on the Eastern
front opened his eyes

376
00:22:12.300 --> 00:22:15.233
to the mass murder of Jews and Slavs.

377
00:22:16.333 --> 00:22:19.209
Outraged. the young
officer openly stated.

378
00:22:19.233 --> 00:22:21.676
"They are shooting Jews in masses.

379
00:22:21.700 --> 00:22:24.567
These crimes must not
be allowed to continue."

380
00:22:26.433 --> 00:22:27.976
As well as places like Auschwitz.

381
00:22:28.000 --> 00:22:31.143
which were relatively
easy to keep quite secret.

382
00:22:31.167 --> 00:22:33.676
what people also knew about from troops

383
00:22:33.700 --> 00:22:35.309
returning from the front.

384
00:22:35.333 --> 00:22:37.309
and especially from the Eastern front.

385
00:22:37.333 --> 00:22:40.443
was the Einsatzgruppen.
the mobile killing squads

386
00:22:40.467 --> 00:22:43.009
that went behind the German lines.

387
00:22:43.033 --> 00:22:44.343
killing anybody they regarded as

388
00:22:44.367 --> 00:22:46.809
being an enemy of the Third Reich.

389
00:22:46.833 --> 00:22:49.509
such as Jews and
communists and so on.

390
00:22:49.533 --> 00:22:52.509
And the Einsatzgruppen
killed millions of people.

391
00:22:52.533 --> 00:22:55.676
and it was impossible to keep that quiet.

392
00:22:55.700 --> 00:22:58.609
Stauffenberg became
so vocal in his criticism.

393
00:22:58.633 --> 00:23:02.409
his officers decided that he
should be posted to Tunisia.

394
00:23:02.433 --> 00:23:04.009
a move which would
end with Stauffenberg

395
00:23:04.033 --> 00:23:07.976
losing his left eye. his
right hand. and two fingers

396
00:23:08.000 --> 00:23:11.067
in a surprise attack by
American fighter aircraft.

397
00:23:15.400 --> 00:23:17.443
Stauffenberg's life-changing injuries

398
00:23:17.467 --> 00:23:19.343
did not hinder his mission

399
00:23:19.367 --> 00:23:22.543
to rid Germany of its ruthless dictator.

400
00:23:22.567 --> 00:23:25.576
Instead. his fate placed him
in an even better position

401
00:23:25.600 --> 00:23:27.533
to implement the plot.

402
00:23:28.367 --> 00:23:30.200
right at the heart of Berlin.

403
00:23:52.000 --> 00:23:54.409
In September. 1943.

404
00:23:54.433 --> 00:23:56.609
Stauffenberg was posted
to the headquarters

405
00:23:56.633 --> 00:23:59.333
of the replacement army
on the Bendlerstrasse.

406
00:24:01.367 --> 00:24:04.676
Here he would be introduced
to two key conspirators.

407
00:24:04.700 --> 00:24:07.143
Major General Henning von Tresckow.

408
00:24:07.167 --> 00:24:09.600
and General Friedrich Olbricht.

409
00:24:11.067 --> 00:24:14.343
The tide of the war was now
turning against Germany.

410
00:24:14.367 --> 00:24:17.700
The trio had to move first
to implement the plot.

411
00:24:21.733 --> 00:24:27.676
We shall defend our island.
whatever the cost may be.

412
00:24:27.700 --> 00:24:32.233
We shall fight on
beaches. landing grounds.

413
00:24:33.300 --> 00:24:37.076
in fields. in streets. and on the hills.

414
00:24:37.100 --> 00:24:39.300
We shall never surrender.

415
00:25:04.200 --> 00:25:06.543
Olbricht put forward a new strategy

416
00:25:06.567 --> 00:25:08.843
for staging a coup against Hitler.

417
00:25:08.867 --> 00:25:11.609
The replacement Army had
an operational plan called.

418
00:25:11.633 --> 00:25:13.143
Operation Valkyrie

419
00:25:13.167 --> 00:25:16.409
to be used in the event of a
breakdown of law and order.

420
00:25:16.433 --> 00:25:19.443
Valkyrie was the perfect way
to mobilize the reserve army

421
00:25:19.467 --> 00:25:21.167
during the takeover.

422
00:25:23.967 --> 00:25:26.043
Tresckow and Stauffenberg
worked tirelessly

423
00:25:26.067 --> 00:25:27.676
to modify Valkyrie

424
00:25:27.700 --> 00:25:30.567
and at the same time
remain undiscovered.

425
00:25:32.333 --> 00:25:36.043
The pair drafted plans
to occupy German cities.

426
00:25:36.067 --> 00:25:39.943
take control of Heinrich
Himmler's SS and Gestapo.

427
00:25:39.967 --> 00:25:42.733
and even arrest the Nazi leadership.

428
00:25:44.800 --> 00:25:47.276
The plotters finalized every tiny detail.

429
00:25:47.300 --> 00:25:49.943
even devising a whole
new government structure.

430
00:25:49.967 --> 00:25:51.700
following takeover.

431
00:25:53.500 --> 00:25:57.176
General Ludwig Beck would
be placed as head of state.

432
00:25:57.200 --> 00:26:00.109
the long-term resistor Dr.
Carl Friedrich Goerdeler

433
00:26:00.133 --> 00:26:02.543
would become Germany's
new chancellor.

434
00:26:02.567 --> 00:26:06.743
Tresckow would take control of
all German security services.

435
00:26:06.767 --> 00:26:08.643
and either Olbricht or Stauffenberg

436
00:26:08.667 --> 00:26:11.000
would serve as state secretary.

437
00:26:12.633 --> 00:26:16.967
The only question that remained
was how to kill Hitler.

438
00:26:20.467 --> 00:26:22.609
There were lots of plots to kill Hitler.

439
00:26:22.633 --> 00:26:26.776
and he survived so many
that it made Hitler feel

440
00:26:26.800 --> 00:26:28.376
that he really did have this

441
00:26:28.400 --> 00:26:30.109
kind of divine providence behind him

442
00:26:30.133 --> 00:26:31.800
that made him survive.

443
00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:35.543
But actually. the most
kind of celebrated plot

444
00:26:35.567 --> 00:26:39.843
against him was the July
Bomb Plot of July. 1944.

445
00:26:39.867 --> 00:26:42.409
in which you've got this kind of cadre

446
00:26:42.433 --> 00:26:45.409
of senior officers all over the Third Reich

447
00:26:45.433 --> 00:26:49.143
who've been meeting in secret
for many years actually.

448
00:26:49.167 --> 00:26:51.176
what they wanna do is to get rid of Hitler.

449
00:26:51.200 --> 00:26:54.709
And they don't want to get rid
of Hitler because he's evil.

450
00:26:54.733 --> 00:26:57.609
that may be part of it.
they want to get rid of Hitler

451
00:26:57.633 --> 00:27:00.176
because they think he's
fighting the war badly.

452
00:27:00.200 --> 00:27:01.809
and they just are fed up with him.

453
00:27:01.833 --> 00:27:03.776
And indeed Hitler is
fighting the war badly

454
00:27:03.800 --> 00:27:07.276
'cause he's a terrible. terrible strategist.

455
00:27:07.300 --> 00:27:10.409
The conspirators
considered poisoning his food

456
00:27:10.433 --> 00:27:14.176
and even shooting the
Führer at a dinner party.

457
00:27:14.200 --> 00:27:16.543
But by late 1943.

458
00:27:16.567 --> 00:27:19.509
Hitler had become increasingly
paranoid and suspicious.

459
00:27:19.533 --> 00:27:24.043
often abruptly changing
plans or tightening access.

460
00:27:24.067 --> 00:27:27.933
In the end. a time bomb
was the only option.

461
00:27:33.033 --> 00:27:34.509
At the time of planning.

462
00:27:34.533 --> 00:27:38.133
none of the conspirators had
direct access to Adolf Hitler.

463
00:27:39.700 --> 00:27:44.167
However. in 1944. everything
changed for Stauffenberg.

464
00:27:45.733 --> 00:27:47.343
General Friedrich Fromm.

465
00:27:47.367 --> 00:27:49.043
the commander of the
replacement Army.

466
00:27:49.067 --> 00:27:52.676
appointed Stauffenberg
as his chief of staff.

467
00:27:52.700 --> 00:27:55.809
Fromm was the only
officer other than Hitler

468
00:27:55.833 --> 00:27:59.033
who could initiate Operation
Valkyrie with his signature.

469
00:28:00.200 --> 00:28:02.543
Aware of his subordinate's plan.

470
00:28:02.567 --> 00:28:04.176
he made a deal to remain quiet

471
00:28:04.200 --> 00:28:06.543
on the condition that
he became a top official

472
00:28:06.567 --> 00:28:09.776
in the new government after the mutiny.

473
00:28:09.800 --> 00:28:11.676
The plan was coming into place.

474
00:28:11.700 --> 00:28:13.709
and Stauffenberg was now in a position

475
00:28:13.733 --> 00:28:16.767
where he could see Hitler
on a regular basis.

476
00:28:18.467 --> 00:28:19.676
Of all the conspirators.

477
00:28:19.700 --> 00:28:23.367
he was the best placed
to become the assassin.

478
00:28:37.300 --> 00:28:39.043
Time was ticking.

479
00:28:39.067 --> 00:28:41.676
Certain defeat in the war closed in.

480
00:28:41.700 --> 00:28:43.809
and the coup needed to take place soon

481
00:28:43.833 --> 00:28:46.667
to save Germany from total destruction.

482
00:28:48.400 --> 00:28:51.609
The Army had posted Tresckow
to the eastern front

483
00:28:51.633 --> 00:28:54.776
and the original assassin.
General Hellmuth Stieff

484
00:28:54.800 --> 00:28:56.567
had backed down from the plan.

485
00:28:57.933 --> 00:29:01.309
Stauffenberg took total
control of the resistance.

486
00:29:01.333 --> 00:29:02.776
but in doing so.

487
00:29:02.800 --> 00:29:05.343
he placed himself as both the
assassin and the commander

488
00:29:05.367 --> 00:29:07.833
of the Valkyrie Operation in Berlin.

489
00:29:14.867 --> 00:29:18.443
Hidden away in the dark
shadows of the Masurian woods.

490
00:29:18.467 --> 00:29:20.209
Hitler was gathering
his most trusted offices

491
00:29:20.233 --> 00:29:23.633
for a military conference
at the Wolfsschanze.

492
00:29:24.900 --> 00:29:27.443
It was the 20th of July. 1944.

493
00:29:27.467 --> 00:29:29.109
and Stauffenberg found himself

494
00:29:29.133 --> 00:29:31.209
in the Eastern front headquarters.

495
00:29:31.233 --> 00:29:34.467
alongside his aide.
Lieutenant Werner von Haeften.

496
00:29:35.667 --> 00:29:37.109
Briefcase in hand.

497
00:29:37.133 --> 00:29:40.209
the Colonel now had the perfect
opportunity to plant a bomb

498
00:29:40.233 --> 00:29:43.267
that could change the
course of history forever.

499
00:29:44.567 --> 00:29:47.076
So on 20th of July. 1944.
everything's in place.

500
00:29:47.100 --> 00:29:51.876
You've got people in Berlin
ready to take over the SS.

501
00:29:51.900 --> 00:29:56.967
You've got various army units
all over the Third Reich.

502
00:29:58.333 --> 00:30:00.243
ready to go. the drop of
the code word "Valkyrie."

503
00:30:00.267 --> 00:30:03.109
which is gonna say that
Hitler's being killed.

504
00:30:03.133 --> 00:30:07.343
However. the summer sun
had reared its brutal head.

505
00:30:07.367 --> 00:30:09.976
The atmosphere was
intense and uncomfortable.

506
00:30:10.000 --> 00:30:12.276
And irritated by the heat.

507
00:30:12.300 --> 00:30:14.443
Hitler moved the meeting
from the Führerbunker

508
00:30:14.467 --> 00:30:16.200
to a wooden hut.

509
00:30:20.067 --> 00:30:24.676
At 12:30pm. Stauffenberg excused
himself to a nearby room.

510
00:30:24.700 --> 00:30:27.243
claiming he needed to change his shirt.

511
00:30:27.267 --> 00:30:30.833
But in reality. the pair
began fussing the first bomb.

512
00:30:32.300 --> 00:30:34.243
A guard knocked at the door.

513
00:30:34.267 --> 00:30:36.209
urging the colonel to hurry.

514
00:30:36.233 --> 00:30:38.243
Haeften and Stauffenberg panicked.

515
00:30:38.267 --> 00:30:39.776
The Führer was waiting

516
00:30:39.800 --> 00:30:43.576
and no time remained to
fuse the second bomb.

517
00:30:43.600 --> 00:30:45.700
one bomb would have to do.

518
00:30:47.133 --> 00:30:48.809
As the seconds slipped away.

519
00:30:48.833 --> 00:30:51.076
Stauffenberg swiftly excused himself

520
00:30:51.100 --> 00:30:53.533
under the pretext of making a phone call.

521
00:30:58.567 --> 00:31:00.409
But unbeknownst to
the would-be assassin.

522
00:31:00.433 --> 00:31:03.276
Colonel Heinz Brandt
positioned next to Hitler.

523
00:31:03.300 --> 00:31:05.809
inadvertently collided with the briefcase.

524
00:31:05.833 --> 00:31:09.409
deftly nudging it behind a table leg.

525
00:31:09.433 --> 00:31:13.267
The fate of Europe now
hung in the balance.

526
00:31:14.200 --> 00:31:18.076
At 12:42pm. the bomb detonated.

527
00:31:21.767 --> 00:31:24.876
Shock waves reverberated
through the Wolfsschanze.

528
00:31:24.900 --> 00:31:27.409
Stauffenberg and
Haeften quickly escaped

529
00:31:27.433 --> 00:31:29.043
driving to a nearby airfield

530
00:31:29.067 --> 00:31:32.467
to return to Berlin and finish the job.

531
00:31:38.067 --> 00:31:42.800
The hopes of resistance crumbled
as the aftermath unfolded.

532
00:31:45.600 --> 00:31:48.709
Stauffenberg. Olbricht. and Ludwig Beck

533
00:31:48.733 --> 00:31:51.409
rushed to commandeer
various government buildings

534
00:31:51.433 --> 00:31:54.676
and arrested general Fromm
for refusal to cooperate

535
00:31:54.700 --> 00:31:57.676
until Hitler's death had been confirmed.

536
00:31:57.700 --> 00:32:00.700
But soon came the news
they had been fearing.

537
00:32:02.800 --> 00:32:06.443
Hitler was. in fact. very much alive.

538
00:32:06.467 --> 00:32:10.076
As it happened. the furniture
took most of the blast.

539
00:32:10.100 --> 00:32:14.676
and Hitler got away with just
very superficial injuries.

540
00:32:14.700 --> 00:32:17.743
And put into place straight away.

541
00:32:17.767 --> 00:32:22.243
the capture. the arrest.
and then the execution

542
00:32:22.267 --> 00:32:25.876
of all of those who were
involved in that bomb plot.

543
00:32:25.900 --> 00:32:28.909
Had the bomb found
its place to Hitler's left.

544
00:32:28.933 --> 00:32:31.743
had the meeting unfolded
in the Führerbunker.

545
00:32:31.767 --> 00:32:34.843
and had Stauffenberg
triggered both devices.

546
00:32:34.867 --> 00:32:38.100
the assassination success
would've seemed inevitable.

547
00:32:39.500 --> 00:32:42.343
Yet fate intervened.

548
00:32:42.367 --> 00:32:45.176
Hitler emerged with only limited injuries.

549
00:32:45.200 --> 00:32:47.009
sheltered by a table leg

550
00:32:47.033 --> 00:32:49.643
that absorbed the brunt of the blast.

551
00:32:49.667 --> 00:32:54.243
The plan had faltered.
the tables had turned.

552
00:32:54.267 --> 00:32:55.776
The dream of a world without Hitler

553
00:32:55.800 --> 00:32:59.367
slipped through the grasp
of those who dared to defy.

554
00:33:04.867 --> 00:33:06.576
Furious and humiliated.

555
00:33:06.600 --> 00:33:09.843
Hitler ordered commanding
officer Otto Ernst Remer

556
00:33:09.867 --> 00:33:13.943
to arrest the conspirators
and bring them to him alive.

557
00:33:13.967 --> 00:33:17.200
But a bitter general
Fromm had other ideas.

558
00:33:18.033 --> 00:33:19.609
To hide his involvement

559
00:33:19.633 --> 00:33:22.309
from ordered immediate court martials.

560
00:33:22.333 --> 00:33:25.543
the conspirators now faced
swift and brutal reprisals

561
00:33:25.567 --> 00:33:29.809
for their bold attempt to
alter the course of history.

562
00:33:29.833 --> 00:33:34.043
Ludwig Beck asked for a
pistol and shot himself.

563
00:33:34.067 --> 00:33:37.600
the first of many suicide
attempts in the coming days.

564
00:33:39.967 --> 00:33:44.209
At 00:10 hours on the 21st of July. 1944.

565
00:33:44.233 --> 00:33:48.009
Colonel von Stauffenberg.
General Friedrich Olbricht.

566
00:33:48.033 --> 00:33:49.409
Lieutenant Werner von Haeften

567
00:33:49.433 --> 00:33:52.609
and another officer.
Albrecht Mertz von Quirnheim

568
00:33:52.633 --> 00:33:56.367
were killed by firing squad
in the Bendlerblock courtyard.

569
00:33:59.733 --> 00:34:03.076
On the eastern front. Tresckow
learned of the plotters fate

570
00:34:03.100 --> 00:34:05.076
and committed suicide.

571
00:34:05.100 --> 00:34:08.633
Until the end. he remained
loyal to the cause.

572
00:34:09.933 --> 00:34:14.300
The plot to kill Hitler
was well and truly over.

573
00:34:17.800 --> 00:34:19.776
The 20th of July. plot

574
00:34:19.800 --> 00:34:22.143
serves as a testament
to the bravery of those

575
00:34:22.167 --> 00:34:25.343
who dared to stand
against a ruthless regime.

576
00:34:25.367 --> 00:34:28.667
Even in the face of almost
insurmountable odds.

577
00:34:31.900 --> 00:34:33.276
If the plan had succeeded.

578
00:34:33.300 --> 00:34:36.343
it would've undoubtedly
shortened the war by many months

579
00:34:36.367 --> 00:34:39.000
and saved countless lives.

580
00:34:42.433 --> 00:34:45.176
However. Hitler's days
were still numbered.

581
00:34:45.200 --> 00:34:47.109
and he would face the
looming shadow of death

582
00:34:47.133 --> 00:34:49.400
sooner rather than later.

583
00:34:53.233 --> 00:34:55.743
The Russians move
steadily from the East

584
00:34:55.767 --> 00:34:58.233
whilst the western allies
crossed the Rhineland.

585
00:34:59.933 --> 00:35:04.109
By April. 1945. 3 million Soviet troops

586
00:35:04.133 --> 00:35:06.243
dealt brutal blows to the last traces

587
00:35:06.267 --> 00:35:08.467
of the German resistance.

588
00:35:11.300 --> 00:35:13.543
With the Russians at the gates to Berlin.

589
00:35:13.567 --> 00:35:16.576
Adolf Hitler had nowhere to run.

590
00:35:16.600 --> 00:35:18.743
The first half of 1945 is probably

591
00:35:18.767 --> 00:35:21.743
the darkest six months
in Germany's history

592
00:35:21.767 --> 00:35:24.243
because it being invaded by

593
00:35:24.267 --> 00:35:27.143
the Russians. the Red
Army from the East.

594
00:35:27.167 --> 00:35:29.376
and you've got the other allies

595
00:35:29.400 --> 00:35:30.809
coming through from the west.

596
00:35:30.833 --> 00:35:33.543
And it's the Russians
who reach Berlin first.

597
00:35:33.567 --> 00:35:35.400
and when they reach Berlin.

598
00:35:36.533 --> 00:35:38.143
it's a city in rubble. it's a city in flames.

599
00:35:38.167 --> 00:35:39.843
it's a city in chaos.

600
00:35:39.867 --> 00:35:43.809
It's a city in which squads
of marauding loyal Nazis

601
00:35:43.833 --> 00:35:45.976
are going around hanging people

602
00:35:46.000 --> 00:35:48.176
who are not taking part in
the resistance to the city.

603
00:35:48.200 --> 00:35:49.376
It's a city in which

604
00:35:49.400 --> 00:35:52.043
you then got some Nazis
committing suicide.

605
00:35:52.067 --> 00:35:56.343
It is the most benighted.
appalling place you can imagine.

606
00:35:56.367 --> 00:35:57.909
And you've got the Soviet army

607
00:35:57.933 --> 00:36:02.500
literally raping and pillaging this city.

608
00:36:05.167 --> 00:36:07.309
Towards the end of the war. of course.

609
00:36:07.333 --> 00:36:10.109
Hitler was spending more and more time

610
00:36:10.133 --> 00:36:12.843
in his mountain retreat. The Berghof.

611
00:36:12.867 --> 00:36:15.876
And then people were
seeing less of him.

612
00:36:15.900 --> 00:36:18.676
He was making less and
less public appearances.

613
00:36:18.700 --> 00:36:22.109
And then eventually. in
the last months of the war.

614
00:36:22.133 --> 00:36:24.076
into the Führerbunker.

615
00:36:24.100 --> 00:36:28.176
And this is when public
opinion of the Führer

616
00:36:28.200 --> 00:36:29.909
starts to crumble.

617
00:36:29.933 --> 00:36:32.576
Hitler's last days in the Führerbunker

618
00:36:32.600 --> 00:36:35.876
under the Reich Chancellery
in center of Berlin.

619
00:36:35.900 --> 00:36:40.967
are kind of terrible end
of a Shakespearean tragedy.

620
00:36:42.300 --> 00:36:45.176
As the thunder Russian
artillery all around them

621
00:36:45.200 --> 00:36:47.109
and they're deep. deep inside this

622
00:36:47.133 --> 00:36:50.376
sort of concrete underground fortress.

623
00:36:50.400 --> 00:36:54.976
Everybody's sort of kind of
going mad and especially Hitler.

624
00:36:55.000 --> 00:36:58.933
On April the 30th. he
committed suicide in his bunker

625
00:37:00.967 --> 00:37:04.543
as the city at the heart of
his thousandth year Reich

626
00:37:04.567 --> 00:37:08.233
burned to the ground and
crumbled in ruins around him.

627
00:37:11.000 --> 00:37:16.067
The war in Europe ended
forever on May the 7th. 1945.

628
00:37:17.200 --> 00:37:19.100
and Hitler's rule was finally over.

629
00:37:23.300 --> 00:37:25.909
The question
of how much the Germans knew

630
00:37:25.933 --> 00:37:28.209
about what had happened
to the Jewish population

631
00:37:28.233 --> 00:37:29.543
is very complex.

632
00:37:29.567 --> 00:37:31.209
So certainly they knew

633
00:37:31.233 --> 00:37:34.409
that their Jewish compatriots
were disappearing.

634
00:37:34.433 --> 00:37:36.043
being taken away.

635
00:37:36.067 --> 00:37:37.709
They were being taken
away they believed

636
00:37:37.733 --> 00:37:40.709
as indeed some of the Jewish
people themselves believed.

637
00:37:40.733 --> 00:37:45.443
they were taken away
to work in the East.

638
00:37:45.467 --> 00:37:47.043
During the war. word leaked out

639
00:37:47.067 --> 00:37:49.576
from people who had
escaped some camps.

640
00:37:49.600 --> 00:37:53.443
There were aerial pictures
taken of places like Auschwitz.

641
00:37:53.467 --> 00:37:55.843
So. you know. by the middle of the war.

642
00:37:55.867 --> 00:37:59.043
the world at large had a very good idea

643
00:37:59.067 --> 00:38:01.209
that this slaughter was being carried out

644
00:38:01.233 --> 00:38:03.109
on an industrial scale.

645
00:38:03.133 --> 00:38:05.776
Yes. some rumors did circulate back

646
00:38:05.800 --> 00:38:07.309
from soldiers on leave.

647
00:38:07.333 --> 00:38:12.209
and other information did
filter back to the Reich.

648
00:38:12.233 --> 00:38:16.343
But the German population was
busy with facing its own war.

649
00:38:16.367 --> 00:38:20.176
dealing on a day-to-day basis
with the course of the war.

650
00:38:20.200 --> 00:38:23.267
allied bombings.
rationing. food shortages.

651
00:38:26.067 --> 00:38:28.043
There was a deliberate policy
on the part of the Nazis

652
00:38:28.067 --> 00:38:32.076
that this extermination should take place.

653
00:38:32.100 --> 00:38:35.509
not on German soil so these
death camps were all in Poland.

654
00:38:35.533 --> 00:38:38.076
so they were outta the
direct line of vision

655
00:38:38.100 --> 00:38:40.367
of the German population.

656
00:38:43.200 --> 00:38:45.776
When the Germans fully appreciated

657
00:38:45.800 --> 00:38:49.043
what had been done in
their name by the Nazis.

658
00:38:49.067 --> 00:38:51.243
it took a very long time for that to sink in.

659
00:38:51.267 --> 00:38:52.843
If you look at public
opinion polls carried out

660
00:38:52.867 --> 00:38:54.676
in the 40s and the 50s in Germany.

661
00:38:54.700 --> 00:38:58.309
there was still a lot of
residual affection for Nazism.

662
00:38:58.333 --> 00:38:59.843
It was felt that this was something

663
00:38:59.867 --> 00:39:01.843
that had made Germany great again.

664
00:39:01.867 --> 00:39:05.909
It was something that had
got things moving and done.

665
00:39:05.933 --> 00:39:07.809
Yes. there had been excesses.

666
00:39:07.833 --> 00:39:10.609
the small matter of the Holocaust clearly.

667
00:39:10.633 --> 00:39:14.309
But people. some
people in Germany were
willing just to say.

668
00:39:14.333 --> 00:39:18.176
if we can divorce the kind
of genocide bit from Nazism.

669
00:39:18.200 --> 00:39:20.276
you know. is Nazism so bad?

670
00:39:20.300 --> 00:39:22.543
Minority of Germans were still

671
00:39:22.567 --> 00:39:26.400
affectionate towards
Nazism and towards Hitler.

672
00:39:35.167 --> 00:39:37.176
The tyrannical force of Nazi Germany

673
00:39:37.200 --> 00:39:39.433
sent the world into chaos.

674
00:39:41.367 --> 00:39:44.776
An empire of hate.
violence. and discrimination

675
00:39:44.800 --> 00:39:48.376
had spread across the world like a virus.

676
00:39:48.400 --> 00:39:50.443
The atrocities of the Nazi regime

677
00:39:50.467 --> 00:39:53.543
came to popular attention.

678
00:39:53.567 --> 00:39:55.443
Both the Western and the Soviet forces

679
00:39:55.467 --> 00:39:58.743
came to liberate the Nazi camps.

680
00:39:58.767 --> 00:40:01.376
and they were absolutely
shocked and horrified

681
00:40:01.400 --> 00:40:03.776
with what they found.

682
00:40:03.800 --> 00:40:07.476
And once that became known
to the German people as well.

683
00:40:07.500 --> 00:40:10.443
then they were again absolutely
horrified and appalled

684
00:40:10.467 --> 00:40:12.209
about what had been
carried out in their name

685
00:40:12.233 --> 00:40:14.433
by the Hitler dictatorship.

686
00:40:16.000 --> 00:40:18.609
Hitler's rule left a mark on history.

687
00:40:18.633 --> 00:40:22.443
a reminder that this behavior
should never be tolerated

688
00:40:22.467 --> 00:40:23.676
and the world should not dismiss

689
00:40:23.700 --> 00:40:26.167
such brutal atrocities again.

690
00:40:27.567 --> 00:40:28.976
Certainly there are a lot of reasons

691
00:40:29.000 --> 00:40:30.909
why you might have voted
for Hitler in the 30s.

692
00:40:30.933 --> 00:40:34.643
not all of which involved you being evil.

693
00:40:34.667 --> 00:40:36.543
But certainly if you are a fan of Hitler

694
00:40:36.567 --> 00:40:38.209
after the war still.

695
00:40:38.233 --> 00:40:40.343
and after all the revelations
that have come out.

696
00:40:40.367 --> 00:40:43.576
then I would say you definitely are evil.

697
00:40:47.933 --> 00:40:50.076
Today the Valkyrie conspirators

698
00:40:50.100 --> 00:40:52.176
are memorialized as heroes.

699
00:40:52.200 --> 00:40:54.843
even inscribed into the
very geography of Germany

700
00:40:54.867 --> 00:40:56.943
through street names.

701
00:40:56.967 --> 00:40:59.309
A reminder that in times of darkness.

702
00:40:59.333 --> 00:41:02.609
there will always be those
brave enough to fight evil

703
00:41:02.633 --> 00:41:04.367
even from the inside.

704
00:41:08.233 --> 00:41:09.467
German guns.

705
00:41:10.333 --> 00:41:12.209
German bombs.
